---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about the Geneseo Jam Fund's mission, board of directors, and partnership with Geneseo Jam Kitchen.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About the Jam Fund</h1>
      <p>Promoting live music in Geneseo, NY since 2023</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        The Geneseo Jam Fund is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization dedicated to promoting
        live music in Geneseo, New York, and the broader Livingston County community. We
        believe that live music strengthens community bonds, supports local culture, and
        enriches the quality of life for everyone.
      </p>
      <p>
        Through the Sunset Concert Series, Tiny Gallery Concerts, and other events, we
        bring free and accessible live music to the community while ensuring fair
        compensation for the musicians who make it all possible.
      </p>

      <h2>Doing More Together</h2>
      <p>
        The Geneseo Jam Fund extends the mission of
        <a href="https://www.geneseojamkitchen.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Geneseo Jam Kitchen</a>,
        a local concert production company, to deliver quality live music to the people of
        Livingston County. As a charitable organization, Geneseo Jam Fund prioritizes
        community-oriented and accessible programming &mdash; notably making the 2025
        Sunset Concert Series free to attend. The fund contracts with area organizations,
        including Geneseo Jam Kitchen, to manage event logistics.
      </p>

      <h2>Board of Directors</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Andrew Mooney</strong> &mdash; Executive Director</li>
        <li><strong>Jeremy Grace</strong> &mdash; Director</li>
        <li><strong>Maggie Lloydhauser</strong> &mdash; Director</li>
        <li><strong>Piper Wadsworth</strong> &mdash; Director</li>
        <li><strong>Nate Grosse</strong> &mdash; Director</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>501(c)(3) Status</h2>
      <p>
        The Geneseo Jam Fund is recognized by the IRS as a tax-exempt 501(c)(3) public charity.
        All donations are tax-deductible to the extent allowed by law.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
